
[1]irritable

   IR'RITABLE, a. [from irritate.] Susceptible of excitement, or of heat
   and action, as animal bodies.

   1. Very susceptible of anger or passion; easily inflamed or
   exasperated; as an irritable temper.

   2. In physiology, susceptible of contraction, in consequence of the
   appulse of an external body.

   In general, there is nothing irritable in the animal body, but the
   muscular fibers.
